\begin_layout Standard
The previous chapter introduced nPIEA as a technique suitable for studies
 in non-equilibrium QFT.
 This chapter explores the symmetry properties of nPIEA.
 In particular, it will demonstrate that global symmetries are not generically
 preserved by truncations of nPIEA.
 The causes of this and the consequences for phenomenology will be reviewed.
\end_layout

